<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-067-052 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 441 215</DOCID><JOURNAL>CAD-CAM International  Sept 1991 v10 n9 p58(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hot spots. (Hardware Review) (Rikadenki's high resolution RY-T111thermal plotter; Plotter Upgrade) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gordon, Martin.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Rikadenki's 11,150 RY-T111 thermal plotter is an average value,offering high-quality plotter performance but poor qualitydocumentation.andP;  The RY-T111 offers A1 400dpi, 16 simulated penwidths, automatic media cutting and the ability to plot twodensities of grey, and solid black.andP;  RY-T111's installation can becomplex, although the three sets of Dip switches enable theplotter to run with most Cad systems.andP;  Documentation is poor anddoes not explain how to set the plotter up for specific packages.andO;The plotter is set up and controlled by the user via 14 controlbuttons and a two-line LCD display.andP;  Plotting quality on bothpaper and film is excellent.andP;  There is a slight tendency for thefilm to buckle when plotting dense areas of black, but differentthermal distortion corrections can be set via the control panelfor film and paper.andP;  One particularly useful feature of theplotter is its ability to work as a printer by altering one of theDip switches.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Rikadenki (Products).andO;Product:   Rikadenki RY-T111 (Plotter) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     EvaluationPlotters.andO;Feature:   illustrationtablephotograph.andO;Caption:   Quick view: Rikadenki RY-T111. (table)Technical specifications. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>